🔧 B MATRIX FOUNDATIONS:
1. B matrices encode P(next_state | current_state, action) relationships
2. Deterministic transitions: actions have certain, predictable effects
3. Stochastic transitions: actions have probabilistic, uncertain effects
4. Multi-action models: different actions create different dynamics
5. Temporal structure: transitions can encode time-dependent patterns
6. State prediction: B matrices enable forward simulation of actions

🚀 PYMDP AGENT INTEGRATION:
7. PyMDP Agent class seamlessly integrates transition models
8. B matrices are central to policy inference and action planning
9. Multi-step policies use repeated B matrix applications
10. Online learning can adapt B matrices from experience
11. Agent behavior emerges from interaction of B, C, and D matrices

